OL,6,FOne of the witnesses also claimed the
OL,7,Fcare home manager would repeatedly
OL,8,Fkiss and cuddle two vulnerable
OL,9,Fpatients.
OL,11,FThat same member of staff also claimed
OL,12,Fto have seen Malcolm lean onto the
OL,13,Frocking chair of another female
OL,14,Fpatient thrusting his hips close to
OL,15,Fher before she told him firmly to stop.
OL,17,FContinuing his evidence the witness
OL,18,Fsaid he had remarked "it's time
OL,19,Fsomeone blew the whistle on him and
OL,20,Fthe next thing is someone had blown
OL,21,Fthe whistle."
